{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/meet-aggi-the-fire-detection-twitter-bot-a1e3089bf7ea", "time": 1683010522.7919931, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/meet-aggi-the-fire-detection-twitter-bot-a1e3089bf7ea/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Meet Aggi the fire detection Twitter bot \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udef0\ufe0f | by Ameen Najjar | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Meet Aggi the fire detection Twitter bot \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udef0\ufe0f", "description": "@AggiBot is a Twitter bot that uses latest Landsat-8 satellite imagery to detect and visualize active fire. It\u2019s live on Twitter now. I decided to build Aggi back in 2018 when I first saw pictures of\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://twitter.com/aggibot", "anchor_text": "@AggiBot", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landsat_8", "anchor_text": "Landsat-8", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_California_wildfires", "anchor_text": "California wildfires", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sentinel-2", "anchor_text": "Sentinel-2", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landsat_8", "anchor_text": "Landsat-8", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "http://twitter.com/aggibot", "anchor_text": "@AggiBot", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/aggibot", "anchor_text": "@AggiBot", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/aggibot", "anchor_text": "@AggiBot", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Web_Services", "anchor_text": "AWS", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://registry.opendata.aws/landsat-8/", "anchor_text": "Landsat\u2019s S3 bucket", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://rasterio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/", "anchor_text": "Rasterio", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://opencv.org/", "anchor_text": "OpenCV", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20200703_22/", "anchor_text": "Nishinoshima \u897f\u4e4b\u5cf6 volcanic eruption in", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mato_Grosso", "anchor_text": "Mato Grosso, Brazil", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://goo.gl/maps/FH4CDLHCiXhE7zhR9", "anchor_text": "location", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/aggibot/status/1271007303060381698", "anchor_text": "June 10th", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/aggibot/status/1276860038255083522", "anchor_text": "June 26th", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://www.google.com/maps/place/10%C2%B030'48.6%22S+53%C2%B030'19.8%22W/@-10.5148753,-53.5442332,14162m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0x0!8m2!3d-10.5135!4d-53.5055?shorturl=1", "anchor_text": "vegetation", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deforestation_of_the_Amazon_rainforest", "anchor_text": "some form of rainforest deforestation", "paragraph_index": 8}], "all_paragraphs": ["@AggiBot is a Twitter bot that uses latest Landsat-8 satellite imagery to detect and visualize active fire. It\u2019s live on Twitter now.", "I decided to build Aggi back in 2018 when I first saw pictures of California wildfires circulating on Twitter. I wondered if this could be automated somehow using coding, algorithms and satellites!", "In remote sensing, Near infrared (NIR) and Short Wave infrared (SWIR) bands are commonly used for visualizing active fires and/or burn scars. So I started experimenting with NIR/SWIR bands from both Sentinel-2 and Landsat-8 satellites. Data from both missions are open and have very similar spectral profiles (See Figure 1). My initial experiments showed promising results for both. However, more consistent results obtained with Landsat-8 data so I ended up using it in the final product.", "@AggiBot analyzes latest Landsat-8 imagery looking for active fires. Whenever a fire is detected a visualization of the fire is posted to Twitter (See Figure 2 for an example).", "Currently @AggiBot monitors 15M+ square kilometers of land in 13 different countries (See Figure 3). The goal is to expand to monitor at least 10% of earth\u2019s land area, or 51M+ square kilometers.", "@AggiBot is running on AWS so it\u2019s constantly listening to SNS notifications coming from Landsat\u2019s S3 bucket. Every time a new scene is pushed, the following sequence of events is automatically triggered:", "Source code is completely written in Python using libraries such as Rasterio and OpenCV.", "Just last week the Nishinoshima \u897f\u4e4b\u5cf6 volcanic eruption in Ogasawara, Tokyo, Japan was detected on July 4th (See Figure 4).", "Another interesting example comes from Mato Grosso, Brazil where fire at this location was detected on both June 10th and June 26th. Judging from the burn patterns and the appearance of vegetation on Google Maps it seems like some form of rainforest deforestation (See Figure 5).", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fa1e3089bf7ea&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fmeet-aggi-the-fire-detection-twitter-bot-a1e3089bf7ea&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fmeet-aggi-the-fire-detection-twitter-bot-a1e3089bf7ea&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-stor